item.title: Great way to get magic levels!
item.dc:creator: @Greg_the_Xeno Greg the Xeno
item.description:
@Greg_the_Xeno wrote:

[quote=“Taharok, post:13, topic:263262”][quote author=Greg the Xeno link=topic=347734.msg2694655#msg2694655 date=1236190051]

jagex’s anti-macro would detect it cause its predictable.

Completely untrue. Ever used a laptop with the buttons separated from the touch-pad? I do, and back in the day when I used to play rs, I only pressed the button over and over again; never got banned.

Let me rephrase myself: With every macro there is a chance of a ban. And in some sense I am correct, it would be predictable. Every 1.3 seconds between clicks, for example, jagex would catch on. I doubt you where hitting you left click button on a set interval. Unless if you are a ROBOT! O.o

Then you have either have never heard of rsbot or have no idea why it’s so good. It’s base on randomization which makes it as unpredictable as a human.

I hope your not aiming that at me, if so…

If you watch the youtube video you’d know what I was talking about. I’ve used RSbot since forever or at least the last 12-14 revisions since #533.
[/quote]

You were implying that every macro is uniformed in its automated actions, thus allowing some anti-macro system to catch on easily. I then in turn said that you must not have heard of RSBot before, because RSBot uses randomization to stay as random and unpredictable as a human being, making it nearly impossible to predict.[/quote]
Sorry i’m bad with my words lol. I was trying to refer to the idea in the video.

Read full topic

Then you have either have never heard of rsbot or have no idea why it’s so good. It’s base on randomization which makes it as unpredictable as a human.
